    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 2833: Furthest Point From Origin (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a string moves where 'L' means move left, 'R' means move right, and '_' means you can move
                either left or right. Starting from the origin (position 0), execute all moves and determine the
                furthest distance from the origin you can achieve. Return the maximum possible distance.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: moves = "L_LL_R__R"<br>
                Output: 3<br>
                Explanation: Count L's (3) and R's (2). You have 3 wildcards. Assign all wildcards to the dominant
                direction (left) to maximize distance: 3 + 3 - 2 = 4 left, or assign differently. The maximum absolute
                distance is 3.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int furthestDistanceFromOrigin(string moves) 
    {
        int n = moves.size();
        int leftCnt = 0, rightCnt = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            if(moves[i] == 'L') leftCnt++;
            else if(moves[i] == 'R') rightCnt++;
        }
        // assign all '_' to the dominant side
        if(leftCnt &lt; rightCnt) rightCnt = n - leftCnt;
        else leftCnt = n - rightCnt;
        return abs(leftCnt - rightCnt);
    }
};</code></pre>
